USA Gymnastics supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and recognizes the absolute necessity for the Olympic community to work to create a safe environment for all its athletes.
We agree with what the USOC has stated, that is, the interests of our athletes and our clubs, and their sport, can be better served by pushing forward a significant change within our organization, and not with decertification.
USA Gymnastics has launched an independent investigation to understand how an abuse of the magnitude described so courageously by those who managed to survive Larry Nassar remained hidden for so long, and is willing to implement any necessary or appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible, so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a reliable, positive, and accountable environment.
