They discovered that the functioning of the Sun is based on the same basic principles as other stars: the activity of all the stars in the solar system is determined by nothing more than their brightness and rotation.
Brightness is used together with rotation to define a star's Rossby number, which is related to the flow of plasma.
The lower the Rossby number, the less active the star is in relation to magnetic reversals.
