The 802.11n standard can operate both in the 2.4Ghz band and in the 5.0Ghz band.
Assuming that the base station has dual radios, this will allow it to be backward compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g.
The 802.11n speeds are considerably higher than those of previous versions, with a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbps.
